1
00:01:55,239 --> 00:01:55,859
You two.

2
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:57,959
For the Murder Mystery Game this weekend,

3
00:01:57,959 --> 00:01:59,200
don't count me in.

4
00:02:00,060 --> 00:02:00,760
Why not?

5
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:02,560
You had a great time last time.

6
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:03,680
It was fun.

7
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,640
But this weekend,

8
00:02:06,099 --> 00:02:09,620
the Grand Theatre is staging the Bolshoi's *Don Quixote*.

9
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,120
I'm going to see it.

10
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:12,919
The Bolshoi?

11
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:13,740
Yes.

12
00:02:13,860 --> 00:02:14,560
Who is that?

13
00:02:14,599 --> 00:02:15,979
It's the Bolshoi Theatre of Moscow.

14
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,840
You're going to Moscow?

15
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:18,259
Me?

16
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,120
No.

17
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:22,020
Moscow...

18
00:02:22,060 --> 00:02:23,879
It's in Russia, isn't it?

19
00:02:24,219 --> 00:02:25,020
Well,

20
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,240
like the stutterer driving a cart,

21
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,639
who drove all the way to Moscow.

22
00:02:29,340 --> 00:02:31,400
I could say I've been to Moscow.

23
00:02:31,599 --> 00:02:32,840
You've driven a cart?

24
00:02:33,099 --> 00:02:34,560
I used to be a stutterer.

25
00:02:37,659 --> 00:02:38,379
This time,

26
00:02:39,060 --> 00:02:42,300
the Bolshoi Ballet is coming to China.

27
00:02:43,199 --> 00:02:44,460
The Bolshoi...

28
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,439
Since I was little,

29
00:02:46,919 --> 00:02:49,780
it's been my absolute favorite ballet company.

30
00:02:51,180 --> 00:02:52,479
It's such a rare opportunity.

31
00:02:52,759 --> 00:02:54,639
I love them too. I'll go with you.

32
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,500
The thing is, Boss Li,

33
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,780
if you want to go,

34
00:02:57,780 --> 00:02:59,580
I'm afraid the tickets are sold out.

35
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:02,280
Three days ago,

36
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,419
I asked Wang Song

37
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:05,479
to buy tickets for me online.

38
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,919
I don't know if he managed to get them.

39
00:03:08,919 --> 00:03:10,319
He definitely got them.

40
00:03:10,379 --> 00:03:12,120
Wang Song is absolutely reliable.

41
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,080
I trust him completely.

42
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,240
The other day,

43
00:03:15,319 --> 00:03:16,240
he said he'd help me

44
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,780
clean up the junk files on my computer.

45
00:03:17,819 --> 00:03:18,439
We agreed

46
00:03:18,479 --> 00:03:20,539
he'd bring it back today when he's done.

47
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:23,780
Careful.

48
00:03:23,780 --> 00:03:24,280
Auntie Cai,

49
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:25,340
careful.

50
00:03:27,819 --> 00:03:29,219
Why did you let go before it touched the ground?

51
00:03:29,219 --> 00:03:30,080
It wasn't me.

52
00:03:30,759 --> 00:03:31,599
It's fine.

53
00:03:31,620 --> 00:03:32,039
Later,

54
00:03:32,039 --> 00:03:32,719
we can just change,

55
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:33,500
change the pot.

56
00:03:35,319 --> 00:03:36,120
Wang Song,

57
00:03:36,939 --> 00:03:38,599
about what I asked you to buy,

58
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,199
the Bolshoi tickets,

59
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:41,620
what row and seat are they?

60
00:03:42,340 --> 00:03:42,979
Getting tickets...

61
00:03:43,139 --> 00:03:43,719
I forgot.

62
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,520
Darn it.

63
00:03:47,099 --> 00:03:48,080
There isn't a single one left.

64
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,740
Wang Song,

65
00:03:50,159 --> 00:03:50,620
I...

66
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:53,580
I told you three days ago!

67
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:55,340
I'm sorry, Ms. Liu.

68
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:57,039
I've been a bit...

69
00:03:57,879 --> 00:03:58,560
It's my fault.

70
00:03:59,039 --> 00:04:00,500
Forget it. It's okay.

71
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:01,500
Well,

72
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:03,259
the cart won't make it to Moscow either.

73
00:04:04,139 --> 00:04:06,219
My computer is okay, right?

74
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,599
Your computer...

75
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:08,699
It's lost.

76
00:04:09,060 --> 00:04:09,860
What?

77
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:12,259
Didn't you take it

78
00:04:12,259 --> 00:04:13,580
to clear the junk files?

79
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:14,939
Yes.

80
00:04:14,939 --> 00:04:15,919
I forgot.

81
00:04:20,139 --> 00:04:21,000
This kid...

82
00:04:26,879 --> 00:04:28,139
Sounds great

83
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:29,459
Awesome

84
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:30,240
That was amazing

85
00:04:30,319 --> 00:04:31,259
Thank you

86
00:04:31,399 --> 00:04:33,040
I'll edit it tonight,

87
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:35,240
and post it to our community video account later.

88
00:04:35,660 --> 00:04:36,120
Let's see

89
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,220
Should be fine

90
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,120
Darn it

91
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:40,500
I forgot to press the record button

92
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:41,500
It didn't record

93
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:42,899
How could you do that?

94
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:43,540
This...

95
00:04:43,620 --> 00:04:44,360
We did it for nothing

96
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:46,100
Hey, Wang Song

97
00:04:46,459 --> 00:04:47,600
What's up with you these days?

98
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,600
You seem so distracted

99
00:04:48,699 --> 00:04:50,120
No, I... well...

100
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,079
Auntie Cai thinks so too

101
00:04:52,180 --> 00:04:53,660
You've been acting like you lost your soul lately

102
00:04:53,759 --> 00:04:55,120
Wait, did you get dumped?

103
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:57,160
He needs a partner to get dumped

104
00:04:57,399 --> 00:04:59,120
If he's single, what's there to lose?

105
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,920
It's not me

106
00:05:02,439 --> 00:05:04,060
It's my mom and dad

107
00:05:04,139 --> 00:05:04,839
What?

108
00:05:05,139 --> 00:05:06,420
Your parents got dumped?

109
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:08,019
No, what are you talking about?

110
00:05:08,079 --> 00:05:09,399
You don't call it a breakup for parents

111
00:05:09,399 --> 00:05:10,480
That's called a divorce

112
00:05:11,839 --> 00:05:12,959
Your parents are getting divorced?

113
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:14,319
I...

114
00:05:16,819 --> 00:05:17,600
Why?

115
00:05:18,879 --> 00:05:19,939
They just said

116
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:21,300
they don't want to be together anymore

117
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,600
Don't want to be together anymore?

118
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,279
That's the result, not the reason

119
00:05:24,519 --> 00:05:25,500
The reason...

120
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,139
I don't know either

121
00:05:28,019 --> 00:05:29,240
I'm not close with them

122
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:30,819
Not close?

123
00:05:30,819 --> 00:05:32,259
Not close with your parents?

124
00:05:33,699 --> 00:05:33,920
No...

125
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:34,980
No, wait

126
00:05:35,199 --> 00:05:36,399
Listen to me

127
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:39,699
I went to boarding school in the county for middle school

128
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,500
Then boarding school in the city for high school

129
00:05:41,939 --> 00:05:44,060
I worked during breaks to pay for tuition

130
00:05:44,319 --> 00:05:45,939
I rarely went back home

131
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:48,079
And even if I did, I wouldn't see them

132
00:05:48,259 --> 00:05:49,019
The two of them...

133
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:50,740
One does renovation work in Shenzhen

134
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:52,319
The other does cleaning in Chengdu

135
00:05:52,839 --> 00:05:54,160
So we're just not close

136
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:56,740
That makes sense

137
00:05:56,959 --> 00:05:58,939
If it were a long-distance relationship, it'd be over by now

138
00:06:13,259 --> 00:06:14,199
What are you doing?

139
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:15,779
Why are you standing there like a statue?

140
00:06:15,779 --> 00:06:17,660
Bro, cheer up a bit.

141
00:06:17,740 --> 00:06:19,360
It's just your parents getting divorced.

142
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,560
Let them go ahead and divorce.

143
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,259
To find new happiness.

144
00:06:22,879 --> 00:06:24,079
What do you know?

145
00:06:24,339 --> 00:06:26,100
My parents have been divorced for years.

146
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:27,100
And I'm still not used to it.

147
00:06:27,319 --> 00:06:29,439
I still dream about them getting back together.

148
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,600
My folks divorced ages ago too.

149
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,139
But I don't think it's a big deal.

150
00:06:33,220 --> 00:06:33,939
I still

151
00:06:34,079 --> 00:06:35,920
grew up free and strong.

152
00:06:36,199 --> 00:06:36,959
Well,

153
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:39,040
a complete family is still happier, right?

154
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,180
True, true.

155
00:06:40,180 --> 00:06:41,399
Some girls nowadays,

156
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:43,100
once they hear the guy's parents are divorced,

157
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:43,740
they say,

158
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:45,800
this guy must have character flaws.

159
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,000
And won't date him.

160
00:06:47,699 --> 00:06:48,899
I think,

161
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:50,639
no matter how happy the family,

162
00:06:50,639 --> 00:06:52,300
parents will always have conflicts.

163
00:06:52,420 --> 00:06:53,240
At times like that,

164
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:55,579
the child should act as the glue holding them together.

165
00:06:55,899 --> 00:06:57,019
That's why they say,

166
00:06:57,079 --> 00:06:58,899
children are the shackles of marriage.

167
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,040
It's a bond.

168
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:00,779
Alright then.

169
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:03,120
So Wang Song, you should think about it.

170
00:07:03,459 --> 00:07:04,680
Is it possible that you, the bond,

171
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,800
weren't tied tight enough?

172
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:06,500
No,

173
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,939
he barely sees his parents all year.

174
00:07:08,939 --> 00:07:10,019
How can he tie them tight?

175
00:07:10,139 --> 00:07:11,180
I think

176
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:13,019
Wang Song should do something

177
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,439
to stop them from divorcing.

178
00:07:14,699 --> 00:07:15,939
What can I do?

179
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,379
Whenever I try to persuade them,

180
00:07:17,439 --> 00:07:18,740
they just yell over the phone,

181
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:20,120
"It was all for you..."

182
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,220
"...that we didn't divorce sooner."

183
00:07:21,220 --> 00:07:22,339
"Now that you're grown up..."

184
00:07:22,339 --> 00:07:23,120
"...we're done enduring it."

185
00:07:25,660 --> 00:07:26,319
We're screwed.

186
00:07:26,319 --> 00:07:27,259
The computer screen went black.

187
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:28,959
Whose computer is this?

188
00:07:28,959 --> 00:07:29,420
Quick, paper!

189
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:30,560
I'll go get the fire extinguisher.

190
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,160
What's the use of a fire extinguisher?

191
00:07:34,699 --> 00:07:36,180
This old song is still good.

192
00:07:36,180 --> 00:07:36,639
Yeah.

193
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,339
What if we can't get the data back?

194
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,399
Then we're toast.

195
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:40,959
Professor Fan is going to...

196
00:07:42,319 --> 00:07:43,100
Enemy sighted.

197
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,019
I'm retreating.

198
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:44,720
You cover me.

199
00:07:44,779 --> 00:07:45,240
What enemy?

200
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,240
Wang Song, what are you saying?

201
00:07:46,339 --> 00:07:47,120
Wang Song.

202
00:07:47,959 --> 00:07:49,019
Wang Song is here.

203
00:07:49,639 --> 00:07:50,839
Uh, Professor Fan...

204
00:07:50,980 --> 00:07:51,800
Are you busy?

205
00:07:51,939 --> 00:07:52,939
What would I be busy with?

206
00:07:52,939 --> 00:07:54,160
I can't even write my drafts.

207
00:07:54,399 --> 00:07:55,279
I'm idle.

208
00:07:55,759 --> 00:07:56,819
Is the computer fixed up?

209
00:07:57,259 --> 00:07:58,160
It can't be fixed.

210
00:07:59,079 --> 00:08:00,100
Zhu Zhu, what are you saying?

211
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:03,620
It means your computer is toast.

212
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:04,199
Zhu Zhu!

213
00:08:04,899 --> 00:08:05,899
You have such a big mouth.

214
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:07,019
Isn't it all your fault?

215
00:08:07,180 --> 00:08:08,220
For not tightening the bottle cap.

216
00:08:08,259 --> 00:08:09,660
That was just an accident.

217
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,180
Yes.

218
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,639
So a drink was spilled on my computer?

219
00:08:12,699 --> 00:08:13,519
It wasn't spilled.

220
00:08:13,579 --> 00:08:14,279
That's good then.

221
00:08:14,399 --> 00:08:15,519
It was poured right onto it.

222
00:08:15,519 --> 00:08:16,079
Ah!

223
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,240
It started smoking right then.

224
00:08:18,259 --> 00:08:19,319
My drafts!

225
00:08:19,319 --> 00:08:20,740
They're all saved in there.

226
00:08:20,839 --> 00:08:22,279
My life's work!

227
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,680
Professor Fan, don't worry.

228
00:08:24,860 --> 00:08:26,120
I've already sent it for repairs.

229
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:26,699
Right.

230
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:27,579
Most likely...

231
00:08:27,579 --> 00:08:28,500
Very possibly...

232
00:08:28,699 --> 00:08:29,639
Maybe...

233
00:08:29,879 --> 00:08:30,759
It can be fixed.

234
00:08:31,019 --> 00:08:32,019
Maybe?

235
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:34,080
So there's still a chance it can't be fixed!

236
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:35,320
Wang Song.

237
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:37,419
Aren't you usually the most reliable one?

238
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,120
Just because your parents are divorcing...

239
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,720
...it's hit you this hard?

240
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:43,159
Look at how much trouble you've caused these past two days.

241
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:44,639
You kid...

242
00:08:44,639 --> 00:08:46,379
Your mental resilience is too poor.

243
00:08:47,299 --> 00:08:47,980
Old Fan.

244
00:08:48,919 --> 00:08:49,879
You old geezer.

245
00:08:49,879 --> 00:08:51,519
Your mental resilience isn't much better.

246
00:08:52,620 --> 00:08:53,399
Just a broken computer...

247
00:08:53,399 --> 00:08:54,879
...and it's hit you this hard?

248
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:55,940
A broken computer?

249
00:08:56,039 --> 00:08:57,639
All my important data!

250
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,419
The kid's parents are about to divorce.

251
00:08:59,919 --> 00:09:01,419
Isn't that a bigger deal than your thing?

252
00:09:01,519 --> 00:09:02,580
Exactly.

253
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:05,399
The kid is watching his family fall apart.

254
00:09:05,559 --> 00:09:07,139
Anyone who runs into that kind of thing...

255
00:09:07,139 --> 00:09:08,360
...would lose their bearings.

256
00:09:09,559 --> 00:09:11,940
Divorce doesn't necessarily mean the family is broken.

257
00:09:12,279 --> 00:09:13,259
The dad is still the dad.

258
00:09:13,259 --> 00:09:14,279
The mom is still the mom.

259
00:09:14,460 --> 00:09:15,460
That's not the same.

260
00:09:15,559 --> 00:09:16,580
Once they divorce...

261
00:09:16,580 --> 00:09:17,899
...the dad isn't the dad anymore.

262
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,360
He becomes an enemy.

263
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,120
Why?

264
00:09:20,179 --> 00:09:22,340
I'm a living example right here.

265
00:09:22,820 --> 00:09:23,940
Originally, our family...

266
00:09:24,139 --> 00:09:25,840
...had three loved ones.

267
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:28,000
Now we've become three enemies.

268
00:09:28,179 --> 00:09:29,000
They can't divorce.

269
00:09:29,399 --> 00:09:30,659
I don't approve.

270
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:32,039
If there's no love...

271
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,940
...they should separate.

272
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:35,440
Give her freedom.

273
00:09:35,799 --> 00:09:36,940
You foreigner, you don't understand.

274
00:09:36,980 --> 00:09:38,179
If the family is broken...

275
00:09:38,259 --> 00:09:39,860
...what's the point of freedom?

276
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,519
You bachelors...

277
00:09:41,580 --> 00:09:43,399
...simply aren't like us family people...

278
00:09:43,399 --> 00:09:44,299
...who value relationships.

279
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:46,220
You give up too easily.

280
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,360
That's also why you're single.

281
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:50,500
It's precisely because we cherish love...

282
00:09:50,740 --> 00:09:52,960
...that we don't want to send love to its grave.

283
00:09:53,019 --> 00:09:54,059
Right, Ms. Liu?

284
00:09:55,299 --> 00:09:56,120
Ms. Liu

285
00:09:57,039 --> 00:09:58,059
What I said just now

286
00:09:58,059 --> 00:09:59,159
wasn't directed at you.

287
00:09:59,159 --> 00:10:00,440
You value relationships the most.

288
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,299
That's true.

289
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:03,059
We women, compared to men,

290
00:10:03,059 --> 00:10:04,039
just value relationships more.

291
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:04,799
Divorce

292
00:10:04,899 --> 00:10:05,980
happens for just four reasons.

293
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:06,600
Right?

294
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:08,580
Men have wandering hearts.

295
00:10:08,980 --> 00:10:10,519
Men have affairs.

296
00:10:10,820 --> 00:10:12,100
Men find mistresses.

297
00:10:12,679 --> 00:10:13,360
The fourth one...

298
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,580
Men order takeout too?

299
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:14,940
Right.

300
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:15,639
Get lost.

301
00:10:16,419 --> 00:10:18,240
So marriage is a couple's business,

302
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:19,600
but divorce is all us men's fault?

303
00:10:20,279 --> 00:10:21,580
Your situation proves

304
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:23,159
Ms. Cai is right.

305
00:10:23,159 --> 00:10:23,740
You shut up.

306
00:10:23,779 --> 00:10:24,559
Don't bring me into this.

307
00:10:24,759 --> 00:10:25,259
You speak first.

308
00:10:25,259 --> 00:10:26,080
Tell me.

309
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,419
Which couple

310
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:29,179
doesn't have the woman there

311
00:10:29,259 --> 00:10:30,299
mending and sewing,

312
00:10:30,299 --> 00:10:31,500
washing and scrubbing,

313
00:10:31,559 --> 00:10:32,919
suffering hardships,

314
00:10:32,919 --> 00:10:34,039
working without complaint?

315
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:35,500
And you men?

316
00:10:35,980 --> 00:10:36,919
You act like lords.

317
00:10:37,179 --> 00:10:38,259
All talk, no action.

318
00:10:38,379 --> 00:10:39,820
Fighting, domestic violence,

319
00:10:39,879 --> 00:10:41,299
and then having an affair.

320
00:10:41,779 --> 00:10:43,899
What do we women get from you?

321
00:10:44,820 --> 00:10:45,480
So

322
00:10:45,580 --> 00:10:46,320
you're suggesting

323
00:10:46,559 --> 00:10:47,220
a divorce?

324
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:47,620
That's right.

325
00:10:47,679 --> 00:10:48,580
What do you mean "right"?

326
00:10:48,639 --> 00:10:50,559
You can't divorce. You can't.

327
00:10:50,580 --> 00:10:51,539
But you can't force love.

328
00:10:51,539 --> 00:10:53,379
There's a bond between husband and wife.

329
00:10:53,379 --> 00:10:54,779
If I want a divorce, no one can stop me.

330
00:10:55,659 --> 00:10:56,039
But

331
00:10:56,460 --> 00:10:58,600
look at this mess with your parents.

332
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,379
It's got them all worked up.

333
00:11:00,580 --> 00:11:01,919
Women abuse men too.

334
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,019
How can it be like that?

335
00:11:12,759 --> 00:11:14,299
Don't... don't pull me.

336
00:11:14,580 --> 00:11:15,799
Why are you pushing me?

337
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:16,419
No...

338
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:17,259
I'm not pushing you.

339
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:18,000
I'm pulling you back.

340
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,120
You can't do something foolish.

341
00:11:19,159 --> 00:11:20,320
Why would I do something foolish?

342
00:11:20,980 --> 00:11:21,840
Besides, even if I did,

343
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,059
I wouldn't jump in the river.

344
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,240
I was on the school swim team.

345
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:25,940
You know?

346
00:11:26,299 --> 00:11:27,100
That's true.

347
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:29,419
Then what are you doing standing here at night?

348
00:11:29,779 --> 00:11:31,080
None of your business.

349
00:11:31,379 --> 00:11:32,419
Can't I recite English?

350
00:11:34,159 --> 00:11:35,720
But who recites English at night?

351
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:36,720
You have to do it in the morning.

352
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,600
To remember it better.

353
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,899
Why do you keep following me?

354
00:11:52,039 --> 00:11:53,000
Afraid something might happen to you.

355
00:11:53,519 --> 00:11:55,019
Like stuffing myself to death at breakfast?

356
00:11:55,879 --> 00:11:56,539
Stay away from me.

357
00:11:57,620 --> 00:11:58,759
You're nobody to me.

358
00:11:58,759 --> 00:11:59,740
I'm doing this for your own good.

359
00:11:59,740 --> 00:12:01,000
My kindness is treated like dirt.

360
00:12:01,539 --> 00:12:02,879
You bite the hand that feeds you.

361
00:12:04,059 --> 00:12:04,620
Zhu Zhu

362
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:06,220
What's going on?

363
00:12:06,299 --> 00:12:07,480
Who bit the hand?

364
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:08,360
The donkey.

365
00:12:09,639 --> 00:12:10,720
The donkey bit me.

366
00:12:10,940 --> 00:12:11,860
You two elders,

367
00:12:11,980 --> 00:12:13,019
you be the judge.

368
00:12:13,299 --> 00:12:14,820
He wanted to drown himself in the lake.

369
00:12:14,919 --> 00:12:16,360
I risked my life to save him.

370
00:12:16,419 --> 00:12:17,639
Not only is he ungrateful,

371
00:12:17,639 --> 00:12:18,899
but I ended up getting hurt.

372
00:12:19,059 --> 00:12:20,700
If that's not biting the hand that feeds you, what is?

373
00:12:20,820 --> 00:12:22,559
Who? Who wanted to drown themselves?

374
00:12:22,580 --> 00:12:23,379
Are you saying...

375
00:12:23,399 --> 00:12:24,100
Wang Song?

376
00:12:24,639 --> 00:12:25,360
You bet.

377
00:12:25,419 --> 00:12:26,460
If I had been one minute late,

378
00:12:26,460 --> 00:12:27,779
that kid would have gone under.

379
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:28,659
Look.

380
00:12:29,259 --> 00:12:30,159
Look at you, Professor Fan.

381
00:12:31,519 --> 00:12:33,200
If you hadn't scolded him like that yesterday,

382
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,259
would the kid try to drown himself?

383
00:12:36,179 --> 00:12:36,799
This...

384
00:12:37,059 --> 00:12:38,179
Can you blame this on me?

385
00:12:38,940 --> 00:12:40,039
He's just taking things hard.

386
00:12:40,279 --> 00:12:41,360
That's also because...

387
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:43,000
his parents are getting a divorce.

388
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:44,860
Parents divorcing is one thing.

389
00:12:45,399 --> 00:12:46,240
On the other hand,

390
00:12:46,299 --> 00:12:47,860
you didn't exactly help matters.

391
00:12:49,620 --> 00:12:50,580
Help matters?

392
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,220
Help matters.

393
00:12:58,379 --> 00:12:59,019
Wang Song.

394
00:13:01,019 --> 00:13:02,600
Son.

395
00:13:03,620 --> 00:13:04,179
Dad.

396
00:13:04,559 --> 00:13:05,139
Mom.

397
00:13:05,860 --> 00:13:07,120
Why are you two here?

398
00:13:07,940 --> 00:13:09,179
Didn't you send a WeChat message...

399
00:13:09,220 --> 00:13:10,460
asking us...

400
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:12,240
to come tour Beijing?

401
00:13:12,539 --> 00:13:14,419
When did I invite you two...

402
00:13:14,419 --> 00:13:16,039
to come travel in Beijing?

403
00:13:17,639 --> 00:13:18,799
This was my brilliant move.

404
00:13:19,879 --> 00:13:21,179
It was clearly my idea.

405
00:13:21,659 --> 00:13:22,879
Using your WeChat...

406
00:13:23,019 --> 00:13:24,259
to message your parents...

407
00:13:24,340 --> 00:13:25,500
and book tickets to Beijing.

408
00:13:25,940 --> 00:13:27,480
Since when did it become your brilliant move?

409
00:13:27,620 --> 00:13:28,159
Together.

410
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,220
A brilliant move by both of us.

411
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:30,799
Zhu Zhu deserves credit too.

412
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,039
Zhu Zhu.

413
00:13:33,419 --> 00:13:35,720
Wang Song, next time you pick up packages,

414
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:37,220
remember to log out of WeChat on your computer.

415
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:39,340
Luckily I was doing a good deed.

416
00:13:39,399 --> 00:13:40,879
If you had met a bad person...

417
00:13:40,879 --> 00:13:41,100
let me tell you.

418
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:43,000
Did I ask you to do this good deed?

419
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,039
See, what did I tell you?

420
00:13:44,039 --> 00:13:45,039
Bite the hand that feeds you.

421
00:13:45,220 --> 00:13:45,659
You...

422
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:46,440
Wang Song.

423
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,779
Everyone means well.

424
00:13:49,139 --> 00:13:50,100
Your family...

425
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:51,320
lacks communication usually.

426
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:52,779
We invited the two parties here...

427
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:53,840
to sit down and have a good talk.

428
00:13:56,259 --> 00:13:56,759
Okay.

429
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:57,940
Dad.

430
00:13:58,759 --> 00:13:59,279
Mom.

431
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:00,860
Then tell me,

432
00:14:01,740 --> 00:14:02,799
why do you want a divorce?

433
00:14:08,379 --> 00:14:08,879
You say it.

434
00:14:10,299 --> 00:14:11,000
You say it.

435
00:14:11,740 --> 00:14:13,120
Why do I have to speak first?

436
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:15,899
You brought it up first.

437
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:17,700
So of course you should speak first.

438
00:14:17,919 --> 00:14:18,360
I...

439
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:19,860
I can't say it.

440
00:14:19,919 --> 00:14:21,879
If I say it, they'll laugh me to death.

441
00:14:21,879 --> 00:14:22,840
I'm not saying it.

442
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:23,960
You won't say it?

443
00:14:25,659 --> 00:14:26,840
You won't say it?

444
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:27,860
Fine.

445
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:30,820
I won't say it either.

446
00:14:31,940 --> 00:14:32,759
This...

447
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:33,559
Okay.

448
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:35,919
If you won't say it,

449
00:14:36,039 --> 00:14:37,059
then I won't say it either.

450
00:14:37,340 --> 00:14:38,600
Neither of us will speak.

451
00:14:39,799 --> 00:14:40,759
Don't both stay silent.

452
00:14:41,259 --> 00:14:41,840
I'll speak.

453
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:42,320
You guys... Xiao Cai...

454
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:44,419
Do you two know?

455
00:14:44,899 --> 00:14:46,100
This child, Wang Song,

456
00:14:46,159 --> 00:14:47,620
because of your situation,

457
00:14:47,779 --> 00:14:49,820
has been worried sick.

458
00:14:49,919 --> 00:14:51,419
Can't eat, can't sleep.

459
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:52,220
Otherwise,

460
00:14:52,259 --> 00:14:53,299
he wouldn't have... the Professor's...

461
00:14:53,299 --> 00:14:54,620
broken that computer.

462
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:55,759
Do you know inside that computer,

463
00:14:55,820 --> 00:14:58,159
were the Professor's life savings?

464
00:14:58,679 --> 00:14:59,139
Do you know?

465
00:14:59,139 --> 00:15:00,159
His life savings!

466
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:00,919
How much is that?

467
00:15:00,919 --> 00:15:01,700
How much money?

468
00:15:01,740 --> 00:15:03,000
How much do we have to pay?

469
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:03,519
This...

470
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:05,100
We can't afford it.

471
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:06,159
What is this nonsense?

472
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:06,860
Don't...

473
00:15:06,860 --> 00:15:07,580
Don't talk about this.

474
00:15:07,639 --> 00:15:08,379
Don't get sidetracked.

475
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,080
Back to the main topic.

476
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,440
Why the divorce?

477
00:15:17,779 --> 00:15:18,720
Um, you two.

478
00:15:19,159 --> 00:15:20,419
Hard to bring it up, right?

479
00:15:20,820 --> 00:15:21,940
How about this?

480
00:15:22,139 --> 00:15:22,940
Let's talk separately.

481
00:15:23,059 --> 00:15:23,620
Okay?

482
00:15:23,779 --> 00:15:24,279
Okay.

483
00:15:24,279 --> 00:15:24,759
Sure.

484
00:15:24,759 --> 00:15:25,320
I agree.

485
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,259
Don't your legs get numb squatting like that?

486
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:29,799
There are chairs right here.

487
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,100
Sit down, it's more comfortable.

488
00:15:31,799 --> 00:15:32,460
No need.

489
00:15:32,620 --> 00:15:33,200
No thanks.

490
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:34,820
I'll squat.

491
00:15:35,139 --> 00:15:36,139
It's more comfortable.

492
00:15:38,399 --> 00:15:39,120
Mr. Wang.

493
00:15:39,799 --> 00:15:42,019
Let's have a heart-to-heart talk.

494
00:15:43,139 --> 00:15:44,659
I'm a few years older than you.

495
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:46,419
Whether in academics,

496
00:15:46,419 --> 00:15:47,600
experience, or perspective...

497
00:15:47,639 --> 00:15:48,879
Enough, Old Fan.

498
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,240
You just love to brag.

499
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:52,279
What we're dealing with now is

500
00:15:52,279 --> 00:15:53,840
Mr. Wang's marital issues.

501
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:55,059
What experience do you have?

502
00:15:56,139 --> 00:15:57,240
Let me handle this.

503
00:15:57,519 --> 00:15:58,059
I...

504
00:15:58,399 --> 00:15:59,220
have been married a long time.

505
00:15:59,299 --> 00:16:00,039
I've seen a lot.

506
00:16:00,279 --> 00:16:01,299
I've been a leader for years.

507
00:16:01,299 --> 00:16:03,240
I excel at doing ideological work.

508
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:04,500
Enough, Old Li.

509
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,179
You brag even more than I do.

510
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:07,899
You're good at ideological work?

511
00:16:08,659 --> 00:16:09,820
How many couples have you reconciled?

512
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:10,440
I...

513
00:16:11,860 --> 00:16:13,360
Of course, I haven't reconciled a single one.

514
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,039
But I helped them raise their awareness.

515
00:16:16,860 --> 00:16:18,580
So they divorced happily and peacefully.

516
00:16:18,759 --> 00:16:19,759
See?

517
00:16:20,580 --> 00:16:21,820
That's how marriage is.

518
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:22,759
It's going to rain,

519
00:16:22,820 --> 00:16:23,759
and mother will remarry.

520
00:16:23,899 --> 00:16:25,299
Blindly persuading people to stay together

521
00:16:25,659 --> 00:16:26,799
is not the right approach.

522
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:29,019
That's why I say you're cold-hearted.

523
00:16:29,019 --> 00:16:30,240
You've been a bachelor all your life.

524
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:32,080
You can't stand seeing others happy.

525
00:16:32,419 --> 00:16:34,440
They clearly wanted to divorce on their own.

526
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:35,659
How does that make me cold-hearted?

527
00:16:35,659 --> 00:16:36,500
You just are.

528
00:16:38,139 --> 00:16:38,639
You two...

529
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:39,600
My two brothers...

530
00:16:39,679 --> 00:16:40,299
Stop.

531
00:16:40,399 --> 00:16:41,159
Just stop.

532
00:16:41,159 --> 00:16:41,740
You guys...

533
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:43,379
listen to me for a second.

534
00:16:43,460 --> 00:16:44,259
Let me say something.

535
00:16:44,259 --> 00:16:45,539
Okay.

536
00:16:47,039 --> 00:16:48,419
Don't let my situation

537
00:16:48,639 --> 00:16:50,679
hurt your friendship.

538
00:16:52,179 --> 00:16:53,700
My wife...

539
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:56,679
insists on divorcing me.

540
00:16:57,460 --> 00:16:59,419
She insists that I have

541
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,340
someone on the side.

542
00:17:03,419 --> 00:17:05,019
He definitely has someone on the side.

543
00:17:07,140 --> 00:17:08,339
He and that woman

544
00:17:08,460 --> 00:17:09,420
in Shenzhen

545
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,119
working at a construction site.

546
00:17:12,299 --> 00:17:13,220
That woman

547
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:14,220
is named Xiao Cui.

548
00:17:17,099 --> 00:17:18,079
Xiao Cui.

549
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:20,660
A bit like.

550
00:17:21,380 --> 00:17:24,039
When I found out about this,

551
00:17:24,420 --> 00:17:27,099
I was so heartbroken.

552
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:29,779
I really wanted to die.

553
00:17:30,759 --> 00:17:31,920
But then I thought,

554
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:33,339
I really can't die.

555
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:34,819
For the sake of my son,

556
00:17:34,819 --> 00:17:35,880
I have to live.

557
00:17:36,220 --> 00:17:37,079
No matter what,

558
00:17:37,079 --> 00:17:39,099
wait until my son finishes college,

559
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:40,440
then I'll divorce him.

560
00:17:40,839 --> 00:17:41,640
I must divorce him.

561
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:42,319
I'm telling you,

562
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:43,180
I won't stay with him.

563
00:17:43,579 --> 00:17:44,000
You...

564
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:44,799
Xiao Cai.

565
00:17:44,799 --> 00:17:46,599
Xiao Cai, don't be too impulsive.

566
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,160
Listen to me.

567
00:17:50,339 --> 00:17:52,099
About your husband seeing someone on the side,

568
00:17:52,099 --> 00:17:53,140
is that confirmed?

569
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,019
Of course it's true.

570
00:17:55,019 --> 00:17:57,140
My older brother-in-law told me.

571
00:17:57,339 --> 00:17:57,859
Who?

572
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:01,259
My son's father's older brother.

573
00:18:01,559 --> 00:18:02,819
He couldn't stand watching it.

574
00:18:02,819 --> 00:18:03,960
He told me.

575
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:05,700
Said they were at a construction site,

576
00:18:05,700 --> 00:18:07,920
and the two of them just hooked up.

577
00:18:08,660 --> 00:18:09,839
It seems that...

578
00:18:10,019 --> 00:18:11,039
long-term separation

579
00:18:11,079 --> 00:18:12,359
regarding a couple's relationship

580
00:18:12,359 --> 00:18:14,000
indeed has an impact.

581
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:16,140
Big Sister,

582
00:18:18,019 --> 00:18:19,880
you are so understanding.

583
00:18:21,220 --> 00:18:22,559
I see that you two

584
00:18:22,839 --> 00:18:24,359
are educated people, right?

585
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:25,380
Yes.

586
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:29,519
We are all women.

587
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:31,420
It's not easy for any of us.

588
00:18:32,279 --> 00:18:34,839
So I'll just speak what's in my heart,

589
00:18:34,839 --> 00:18:36,599
and tell you everything.

590
00:18:37,279 --> 00:18:38,140
Speak.

591
00:18:38,140 --> 00:18:39,279
You should have said it sooner. Go ahead.

592
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:43,539
My husband and I

593
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:46,599
met through a matchmaker.

594
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:47,460
That's a good thing.

595
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:51,359
We country folk don't have much romance.

596
00:18:51,559 --> 00:18:53,880
We just got married in a daze,

597
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,299
and had children.

598
00:18:56,759 --> 00:18:59,240
I envy you city people.

599
00:19:00,099 --> 00:19:02,140
You love each other,

600
00:19:02,140 --> 00:19:04,480
and have that "soulmate" connection.

601
00:19:06,140 --> 00:19:06,940
I see what happened.

602
00:19:07,099 --> 00:19:09,299
The problem lies with that matchmaker.

603
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:12,019
If you had met a cultured man like me back then...

604
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:14,160
Sis, do I count as a cultured person?

605
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:16,099
My sister says I do.

606
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:18,740
If I had been your matchmaker,

607
00:19:18,779 --> 00:19:19,539
let me tell you,

608
00:19:19,619 --> 00:19:21,579
I guarantee you wouldn't have reached the point of divorce.

609
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:24,920
In the blink of an eye,

610
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:28,019
over twenty years have passed.

611
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:32,559
Oh, the long, slow years.

612
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:36,759
I've never even tasted

613
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:38,660
the flavor of love.

614
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:42,000
Well, you're quite cultured yourself.

615
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:42,559
Right?

616
00:19:42,599 --> 00:19:43,240
Speaking of which,

617
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:45,880
I've finally figured it out.

618
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:48,279
I really can't take it anymore.

619
00:19:48,539 --> 00:19:49,160
Right?

620
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:51,640
I want to catch the tail end of my youth.

621
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:54,880
I want to find my own happiness.

622
00:19:55,099 --> 00:19:56,140
Sister,

623
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:58,779
don't blame me for being blunt.

624
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:01,180
For someone like you,

625
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:03,339
never mind the tail end of youth,

626
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:05,779
even the big toe of youth is gone.

627
00:20:06,259 --> 00:20:08,940
Happiness isn't that easy to find.

628
00:20:08,940 --> 00:20:09,980
I haven't even found it yet.

629
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:11,079
With your conditions...

630
00:20:11,079 --> 00:20:11,680
let me tell you...

631
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,240
What Auntie Cai means is...

632
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:16,079
What Auntie Cai means is,

633
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:18,579
you've been married for over twenty years,

634
00:20:18,839 --> 00:20:20,579
so you should communicate more.

635
00:20:21,579 --> 00:20:23,900
We can't communicate!

636
00:20:24,460 --> 00:20:25,680
As soon as you sleep,

637
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:26,579
as soon as you close your eyes,

638
00:20:26,579 --> 00:20:28,140
you think of your husband

639
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:30,519
being with another woman.

640
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:32,380
It makes you want to vomit.

641
00:20:32,819 --> 00:20:34,319
How can you live like that?

642
00:20:34,359 --> 00:20:35,740
You can't.

643
00:20:35,740 --> 00:20:37,319
The problem is, he hurt you.

644
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:39,059
Right?

645
00:20:39,220 --> 00:20:40,960
He hurt me,

646
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:41,480
you see?

647
00:20:41,539 --> 00:20:43,920
And he just laughs it off.

648
00:20:45,299 --> 00:20:49,819
My life has been nothing but suffering.

649
00:20:51,299 --> 00:20:56,779
Rain falls from the sky,

650
00:20:56,960 --> 00:21:01,720
and my family produced a heartless man.

651
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:03,460
That's right.

652
00:21:03,460 --> 00:21:04,319
Let me tell you, that's enough.

653
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:07,160
What I hate most in this life is...

654
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:08,480
that heartless scoundrel.

655
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:09,579
That ungrateful thing!

656
00:21:10,299 --> 00:21:12,299
Let me tell you, big sisters,

657
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,980
I've lived such a wronged life.

658
00:21:16,839 --> 00:21:18,640
For these twenty-plus years,

659
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:20,559
for the Wang family,

660
00:21:21,259 --> 00:21:22,819
I served the old,

661
00:21:23,079 --> 00:21:24,680
birthed the young,

662
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,299
sewed the new,

663
00:21:27,799 --> 00:21:29,140
mended the old,

664
00:21:29,619 --> 00:21:31,220
cooked the porridge,

665
00:21:31,359 --> 00:21:33,279
and boiled the rice.

666
00:21:34,019 --> 00:21:35,480
And now,

667
00:21:36,119 --> 00:21:39,680
my husband has a woman on the side,

668
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:41,039
and my son...

669
00:21:41,420 --> 00:21:43,960
he isn't even close to me.

670
00:21:44,359 --> 00:21:47,759
What is the point of me living?

671
00:21:48,460 --> 00:21:49,299
Don't cry.

672
00:21:50,339 --> 00:21:52,119
Although I didn't quite catch what you said,

673
00:21:52,519 --> 00:21:54,680
for this kind of ungrateful scumbag,

674
00:21:54,740 --> 00:21:56,339
we must strike him to the ground,

675
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,539
stomp on him ten thousand times,

676
00:21:57,599 --> 00:21:58,440
so that he may never

677
00:21:58,519 --> 00:21:59,319
get a wife again!

678
00:21:59,359 --> 00:21:59,759
Right!

679
00:21:59,759 --> 00:22:01,559
You shouldn't beat him to death with one stick.

680
00:22:01,559 --> 00:22:01,920
Right.

681
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:02,740
Hit him with a few more sticks!

682
00:22:02,740 --> 00:22:03,099
Hit him!

683
00:22:03,099 --> 00:22:04,140
No, you...

684
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:06,200
What I mean...

685
00:22:06,259 --> 00:22:07,720
What we mean is,

686
00:22:08,940 --> 00:22:10,900
it's best if he can be educated and reformed.

687
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:14,920
Where's the guy named Chen?

688
00:22:15,099 --> 00:22:15,640
No.

689
00:22:15,819 --> 00:22:16,759
That guy named Wang.

690
00:22:17,220 --> 00:22:18,200
Where is Wang Shimei?

691
00:22:18,380 --> 00:22:19,079
Where did he go?

692
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:20,720
Little Cai, what are you doing?

693
00:22:20,839 --> 00:22:22,440
Where is Wang Song's dad?

694
00:22:22,700 --> 00:22:23,859
Did he flee to escape punishment?

695
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:24,920
No, he didn't flee.

696
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,019
He's right here.

697
00:22:26,099 --> 00:22:26,579
Come here.

698
00:22:29,819 --> 00:22:30,940
Alright then.

699
00:22:31,059 --> 00:22:32,740
You heartless scoundrel named Wang.

700
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:34,940
So you've got someone on the side, huh?

701
00:22:35,920 --> 00:22:37,160
Tired of the old and want the new, right?

702
00:22:37,740 --> 00:22:39,299
Found yourself a new flame, did you?

703
00:22:40,579 --> 00:22:41,980
You may look ugly,

704
00:22:42,299 --> 00:22:43,880
but you sure dream big.

705
00:22:44,119 --> 00:22:44,619
What?

706
00:22:45,119 --> 00:22:46,119
What new flame?

707
00:22:46,619 --> 00:22:46,980
I...

708
00:22:46,980 --> 00:22:48,220
I don't have anyone on the side!

709
00:22:48,339 --> 00:22:49,839
You still won't admit it?

710
00:22:50,599 --> 00:22:52,619
You think I don't know anything, right?

711
00:22:52,759 --> 00:22:53,819
What do you know?

712
00:22:54,079 --> 00:22:55,000
Xiao Cui.

713
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:56,920
No, you...

714
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,500
Speak up.

715
00:22:58,819 --> 00:23:00,359
Say it in front of everyone.

716
00:23:00,359 --> 00:23:01,519
Who is Xiao Cui?

717
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:03,019
How did you know?

718
00:23:03,099 --> 00:23:04,079
Brother-in-law.

719
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:05,680
Your big brother told me.

720
00:23:07,039 --> 00:23:08,019
Are you...

721
00:23:08,259 --> 00:23:09,579
Is there something going on between you two?

722
00:23:09,660 --> 00:23:11,119
You're talking nonsense.

723
00:23:12,180 --> 00:23:13,180
What is going on with you two?

724
00:23:13,180 --> 00:23:13,660
You...

725
00:23:13,660 --> 00:23:14,440
Shut up, you.

726
00:23:14,579 --> 00:23:15,519
Just stop talking.

727
00:23:15,799 --> 00:23:17,259
Stop slandering people.

728
00:23:17,359 --> 00:23:18,220
Framing an innocent man.

729
00:23:18,500 --> 00:23:19,079
Let me tell you.

730
00:23:19,079 --> 00:23:20,539
First, explain this clearly to me.

731
00:23:20,619 --> 00:23:21,839
What is your relationship with that person?

732
00:23:21,839 --> 00:23:22,880
That one called Xiao Cui.

733
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:26,319
Let me tell you all.

734
00:23:26,539 --> 00:23:27,700
That woman...

735
00:23:27,819 --> 00:23:29,019
named Xiao Cui.

736
00:23:29,140 --> 00:23:30,900
It's absolutely true.

737
00:23:31,279 --> 00:23:32,460
She's at our construction site,

738
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:34,759
an older lady who cooks meals.

739
00:23:35,299 --> 00:23:36,640
She looks even older than you.

740
00:23:37,019 --> 00:23:37,920
Me and her...

741
00:23:38,339 --> 00:23:40,140
there's really nothing going on!

742
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:44,759
That's still your fault.

743
00:23:45,039 --> 00:23:45,759
How is it my fault?

744
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:47,319
Then how do you treat your wife?

745
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:49,220
You show no interest,

746
00:23:49,319 --> 00:23:49,980
no care,

747
00:23:50,039 --> 00:23:50,759
and pay her no attention.

748
00:23:50,980 --> 00:23:52,119
Is it your fault or not?

749
00:23:52,119 --> 00:23:52,779
Yes.

750
00:23:52,839 --> 00:23:54,259
Women need to be cherished.

751
00:23:54,539 --> 00:23:56,279
Wives must be coaxed.

752
00:23:57,119 --> 00:23:58,480
That's you guys.

753
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:01,140
We are out all day long,

754
00:24:01,319 --> 00:24:02,000
working,

755
00:24:02,220 --> 00:24:03,000
earning money,

756
00:24:03,099 --> 00:24:04,480
supporting the family.

757
00:24:05,099 --> 00:24:07,019
How can we be like you city folks,

758
00:24:07,259 --> 00:24:09,240
saying all those sweet words.

759
00:24:13,259 --> 00:24:14,079
Grandpas, Grandmas,

760
00:24:15,359 --> 00:24:16,319
brothers and sisters,

761
00:24:17,579 --> 00:24:18,680
thank you for your trouble.

762
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:20,339
Thanks for caring.

763
00:24:22,059 --> 00:24:23,279
Let me talk to them.

764
00:24:28,940 --> 00:24:29,779
Dad

765
00:24:31,079 --> 00:24:31,680
Mom

766
00:24:33,900 --> 00:24:35,259
Let's drink this

767
00:24:36,859 --> 00:24:37,759
What needed to be said

768
00:24:38,259 --> 00:24:39,500
I've said it all

769
00:24:40,619 --> 00:24:42,799
If you still want to divorce

770
00:24:44,019 --> 00:24:45,859
your son wishes you happiness

771
00:24:50,019 --> 00:24:50,680
Divorce

772
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,160
or not?

773
00:24:57,519 --> 00:24:58,240
No divorce

774
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:01,619
No

775
00:25:01,619 --> 00:25:03,660
I'm not divorcing for the sake of my son

776
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:06,880
But tell me the truth

777
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:09,160
is there really something going on with that woman?

778
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:12,279
She and I are

779
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:14,259
there's really nothing going on

780
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:14,920
And you?

781
00:25:17,779 --> 00:25:19,059
You and my boss

782
00:25:19,900 --> 00:25:21,019
did you have a fling?

783
00:25:21,579 --> 00:25:22,720
What are you saying?

784
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:24,339
That's a horrible thing to say

785
00:25:27,619 --> 00:25:28,579
Mom

786
00:25:30,319 --> 00:25:31,559
It's great you're not divorcing

787
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:33,819
But even if you don't divorce

788
00:25:34,259 --> 00:25:35,160
our family

789
00:25:35,460 --> 00:25:37,420
needs to make some changes

790
00:25:37,759 --> 00:25:38,880
Starting with me

791
00:25:39,119 --> 00:25:40,140
Start what?

792
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:41,960
Start communicating

793
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:43,039
Start talking

794
00:25:43,039 --> 00:25:45,140
Start caring for each other

795
00:25:45,259 --> 00:25:47,940
Saying "I love you"

796
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:52,059
Our family

797
00:25:52,059 --> 00:25:53,160
the three of us

798
00:25:53,619 --> 00:25:54,779
it's really sad

799
00:25:55,559 --> 00:25:57,720
Three people in three places

800
00:25:59,759 --> 00:26:01,220
Son, you don't know

801
00:26:02,019 --> 00:26:03,380
your dad and I

802
00:26:03,559 --> 00:26:04,599
out there

803
00:26:05,359 --> 00:26:08,140
working day and night

804
00:26:08,460 --> 00:26:10,940
I just wanted to earn more money

805
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:13,039
to put you through college

806
00:26:13,039 --> 00:26:15,299
You must make something of yourself

807
00:26:15,299 --> 00:26:16,440
You know?

808
00:26:17,299 --> 00:26:18,200
I know

809
00:26:20,259 --> 00:26:21,519
I'm graduating soon too

810
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:23,799
You won't need to support me anymore

811
00:26:24,559 --> 00:26:25,519
On the contrary

812
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,579
I'll go to work

813
00:26:27,799 --> 00:26:28,619
work overtime

814
00:26:28,900 --> 00:26:29,759
take part-time jobs

815
00:26:30,559 --> 00:26:31,460
for our family

816
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:32,559
for you guys

817
00:26:32,819 --> 00:26:33,619
to make you proud

818
00:26:34,519 --> 00:26:35,140
Good

819
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:36,539
I

820
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:39,160
I'm not working in Shenzhen anymore

821
00:26:40,259 --> 00:26:41,559
I'm going back to our hometown

822
00:26:44,900 --> 00:26:47,900
Didn't you say my cooking was good?

823
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:49,460
The two of us

824
00:26:49,700 --> 00:26:51,500
we'll open a home-style restaurant

825
00:26:52,099 --> 00:26:52,619
Right

826
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:54,559
Your mom's home-style cooking

827
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:55,900
is delicious

828
00:26:56,339 --> 00:26:58,299
We'll open a home-style restaurant

829
00:26:58,579 --> 00:27:01,059
A second venture

830
00:27:02,119 --> 00:27:04,680
You've never even had a first venture

831
00:27:05,700 --> 00:27:06,940
Let me tell you

832
00:27:07,940 --> 00:27:09,519
when our son makes money later

833
00:27:10,059 --> 00:27:11,019
you two

834
00:27:11,319 --> 00:27:14,059
just stay home and enjoy life

835
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:17,900
Your dad and I aren't going anywhere

836
00:27:17,980 --> 00:27:20,619
The three of us will be together every day

837
00:27:21,460 --> 00:27:22,140
Come on

838
00:27:22,460 --> 00:27:23,019
Cheers

839
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:23,740
Cheers
